{
  "doc_id": "18067",
  "text": "However, the generation capability itself is characterized by inefficiencies in the power plants due to their deteriorating conditions (Fardoun, Ibrahim, Younes, and Louahila-Gualous [CITATION_1] ). The high degree of electrification combined with the estimated electricity demand growth suggests that Lebanon needs to both optimize the current electricity system and increase the installed capacity. However, policy makers and industry specialists have deemed the solution to increase the installed capacity unrealistic, given the weak underlying economic conditions in Lebanon (El-Fadel, Hammond, Harajli, Jones, Kabakian, and Winnett [CITATION_2] ).",
